table_interp module¶

Determines all valid interpretations (sets of pronoun chains) for given tree.

table_interp.interpret(nnodes)¶

Determines all valid interpretations (sets of pronoun chains) for a list of N-nodes, following binding constraints.

Parameters

nnodes (list[Node]) – List of N-nodes from a parse tree

Returns

List of valid interpretations, where each interpretation is a list of chains

Return type

list[list[list[Node]]]
